          <msContents>
            <summary>Praise of 108 names of the Hindu deity Dattātreya a composite, three-headed god representing the triad of Śiva, Viṣṇu, and Brahamā, especially popular in Maharashtra. Text employed in private and public worship and prayer toward this deity through mantras and promised abundance in this world and release (mokṣa) from this world after death.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Dattātreyāṣṭottaraśatanāmastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">दत्तात्रेयाष्टोत्तरशतनामस्तोत्र</title>
